#Dashboard Components & Business Interpretation

1. Total Trucking Companies in Texas (KPI)
Metric: Count of DOT_NUMBER

What it shows:
Total number of registered trucking companies operating in Texas

Marketing Value:
Establishes overall market size
Used as a denominator for penetration, saturation, and growth metrics

2. City-Level Slicer & High-Density Regions

Fields Used:
CARRIER_MAILING_CITY
DOT_NUMBER

What it shows:
Cities with the highest concentration of trucking companies
Interactive filtering allows focus on specific metro areas (e.g., Houston, Dallas)

Marketing Insights:
High-density cities → brand awareness & competitive marketing
Medium-density cities → lead generation & outbound campaigns
Low-density but growing cities → early-mover opportunity

3. Type of Carrier Operation

Field: CARRIER_OPERATION

FMCSA Definitions:
A - OPERATION / CARRIER / INTERSTATE
B - OPERATION / CARRIER / INTRASTATE / HAZMAT
C - OPERATION / CARRIER / INTRASTATE / NONHAZMAT

4. Fleet Size / Power Units Distribution

Field: FLEETSIZE

FMCSA Fleet Size Codes Explained:

Code	Meaning
A	1–2 Power Units
B	3–5 Power Units
C	6–10 Power Units
D	11–20 Power Units
E	21–50 Power Units
F	51+ Power Units

Business Interpretation:
Majority of Texas carriers fall into Fleet Size A & B
Market is highly fragmented and owner-operator driven

Marketing Strategy:
Fleet A–B: Google Search Ads, SMS, cold calling, startup bundles
Fleet C–D: Email marketing, retargeting, bundled service offers
Fleet E–F: Account-based marketing, LinkedIn, long-term contracts

5. Hazmat Carriers

Field: HM_IND

FMCSA Definitions:
Y – Carrier is authorized to transport hazardous materials
N – Carrier is not authorized to transport hazardous materials

Marketing Implications:
Hazmat carriers have:
Higher compliance burden
Higher insurance premiums
More regulatory complexity

Targeting Strategy:
Hazmat = premium services, compliance consulting, insurance optimization
Non-Hazmat = volume-based, cost-sensitive offerings

6. Yearly New Company Registrations in Texas

Metric: Count of DOT_NUMBER by Authority Year
What it shows:
Long-term trend of new trucking company formation
Sharp growth post-2010 and post-2020

Business Insights:
Market entry is cyclical and economically sensitive
New authorities represent highest-intent marketing leads

Recommended Use:
Prioritize companies formed in the last 30–90 days
Align ad spend with historical spikes in registrations
